TP7 : Preuve de programmes impératifs


Exercice 1 (Sémantique):



Question 1 : if x >= 0 then y := x else y := -x



1/

 (x,2) ∈ E               0 ∈ Z            				     (x,2) ∈ E
------------- V     --------------- Z                                     ---------------- V
 E ⊢ x -> 2	     E ⊢ 0 -> 0                         y ∈ dom(E)          E ⊢ x -> 2
---------------------------------- >=		    --------------------------------------- :=
	E ⊢ x >= 0 -> T					E ⊢ y := x -> (x,2), (y,2)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- if-true
		E = (x, 2), (y, 0) ⊢ if x >= 0 then y := x else y := -x 



2/

									 (x,-2) ∈ E
								     ----------------- V
  (x,-2) ∈ E               0 ∈ Z 					E ⊢ x -> -2
------------- V     --------------- Z 			              -------------- (-)
   E ⊢ x -> -2	      E ⊢ 0 -> 0		   y ∈ dom(E)          E ⊢ -x -> 2
------------------------------------ >=          ------------------------------------ :=
	E ⊢ x >= 0 -> ⊥				    E ⊢ y := -x -> (x,2), (y,2)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------if-false
	E = (x, -2), (y, 0) ⊢ if x >= 0 then y := x else y := -x  -> (x,2), (y,2)




Question 2 : while i < 3 do (x := x + i;i := i + 1)



  (i,1) ∈ E		   3 ∈ Z
--------------- V   ------------------ Z
  E0 ⊢ i -> 1	      E0 ⊢ 3 -> 3
------------------------------------- <
  E0 ⊢ i < 3 -> T				(1)			(2)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- while-T
	E0 = (i,1), (x,0) ⊢ while i < 3 do (x := x + i;i := i + 1) ->




Exercice 2 (Logique de Hoare) :




Question 1 :

P(z) = (z = 1)
e = x + 1
P(e) = (x + 1 = 1)
P(x) = (x = 1)


------------------------------------------------------ :=	-------------------------------------------------------- :=
  {x + 1 = 1} x := x + 1 {x = 1} x = 0 => x + 1 = 1		   {x + 1 = 2} x := x + 1 {x = 2} x = 1 => x + 1 = 2	
------------------------------------------------------ Aff       -------------------------------------------- Aff
            {x = 0} x := x + 1 {x = 1}					    {x = 1} x := x + 1 {x = 2}
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- ;
				{x = 0} x := x + 1; x := x + 1 {x = 2}




Question 3 :



	    P(z) = (z = 1)								P(z) = (z = 1)
------------------------------------------- :=              ---------------------------------------------------------- :=
  {1 = 1} y := 1 {y = 1} x >= 0 => 1 = 1			{2 = 1} y := 2 {y = 1} x >= 0 ∧ ¬(x >= 0) => 2 = 1
------------------------------------------- Aff             ---------------------------------------------------------- Aff
  {x >= 0} y := 1 {y = 1}			                     {(x >= 0) ∧ ¬(x >= 0)} y := 2 {y = 1}
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- if
			{x >= 0} if x >= 0 then y := 1 else y := 2 {y = 1}





















